    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1219285814" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14634162091869008645"> <img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1430763155i/14759350.jpg' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>Hayy Ibn Yaqzan, a philosophical tale by Ibn Tufayl is one of those books that the West chooses to ignore which is just as well as the East doesn&apos;t seem to be reading it either. This is okay.<br/><br/>Hayy Ibn Yaqzan is a book that chooses its own readers.<br/><br/>If the words autodidact, solitude, intuition, sublime delight, desert island, social isolation, and the human condition are words that you find yourself automatically drawn to, then there is a good chance that this book might choose you. <br/><br/>If you believe </span>
  <span id="freeText14634162091869008645" style="display:none"> <img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1430763155i/14759350.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>Hayy Ibn Yaqzan, a philosophical tale by Ibn Tufayl is one of those books that the West chooses to ignore which is just as well as the East doesn't seem to be reading it either. This is okay.<br><br>Hayy Ibn Yaqzan is a book that chooses its own readers.<br><br>If the words autodidact, solitude, intuition, sublime delight, desert island, social isolation, and the human condition are words that you find yourself automatically drawn to, then there is a good chance that this book might choose you. <br><br>If you believe in the signficance of the number 7 then you may be interested in learning the secrets of "oriental philosophy". But first, let us please do away with all these Latinized names and call these Muslim philosophers by their own names: Al-Farabi, Ibn Sina, Al-Ghazali, Ibn Bajja, Ibn Tufayl, Ibn Rushd....<br><br>If you are chosen then you will learn to "see potentially", and you will come to understand <br>"what no eye has seen or ear heard, nor has it entered into the heart of man to conceive. So listen now with the ears of your heart and look sharp with the eyes of your mind for what I shall try to convey to you. Perhaps in what I say you will find guideposts to set you on the main road."<br><br>But first ask yourself- What would you do if you were stranded on a desert island?</span>
