    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2801172271" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2801172271" />
    <a title="Aung Sett Kyaw Min" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/52918291-aung-sett-kyaw-min"><img alt="Aung Sett Kyaw Min" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1515573087p2/52918291.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2801172271?book_show_action=true">Apr 27, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Aung Sett Kyaw Min" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Aung Sett Kyaw Min" href="/user/show/52918291-aung-sett-kyaw-min">Aung Sett Kyaw Min</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/25634799-ibn-tufayl-s-hayy-ibn-yaqzan">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2801172271" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11417340396456535181">The essential lesson of the rational-mystic Hayy Ibn Yaqzan&apos;s failed attempt to teach the religious masses of the mystical path to renion with the everliving One is that spiritual awakening cannot be accomodated within the apparatus of organized religion. For Codified rituals, laws, and symbols all intervene and mediate between Truth and the community of believers on Earth with the interest of social cohesion and harmony in mind; they do not reflect Truth as a mirror would reflect the brilliance</span>
  <span id="freeText11417340396456535181" style="display:none">The essential lesson of the rational-mystic Hayy Ibn Yaqzan's failed attempt to teach the religious masses of the mystical path to renion with the everliving One is that spiritual awakening cannot be accomodated within the apparatus of organized religion. For Codified rituals, laws, and symbols all intervene and mediate between Truth and the community of believers on Earth with the interest of social cohesion and harmony in mind; they do not reflect Truth as a mirror would reflect the brilliance of the sun. The multitude wallow in the bowels of organized religion, driven and agitated by the hope to catch a glimpse of the spiritual esctasy that accomplished rational mystics can readily achieve by sheer will and concentration. Of course, it is open to question to what extent the mystic-ascetic regimen of hybrid contemplation (positive + aphophantic) of the Necessary Existent/the bestower of Forms, and shearing oneself of material attachments is as universal as Ibn Tufayl claims it is. The worry here is that the sort of universal immediacy promised by rational mysticism may turn out to be nothing more than a particular and mediated understanding deluding itself into thinking it was a universal...<br /><br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="11417340396456535181" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


