    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2745104593" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2745104593" />
    <a title="Rami Hamze" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/93563862-rami-hamze"><img alt="Rami Hamze" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1551371599p2/93563862.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2745104593?book_show_action=true">Mar 10, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rami Hamze" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rami Hamze" href="/user/show/93563862-rami-hamze">Rami Hamze</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/93563862-rami-hamze?shelf=arabic">arabic</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/93563862-rami-hamze?shelf=2018">2018</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2745104593" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16096121381245563442">Philosophical novel from 12th century by Ibn Tufail about a baby born and raised by a deer on an isolated island without any human interaction. The character’s thought process and culture evolution summarize that of humankind from fig leaf moment to faith. Major theme is that all roads lead to god. A controversial view is that Ibn Tufail was an atheist and meant the total opposite, i.e. human civilizations will always create a god of their own even if they start fresh on an island. Short and eas</span>
  <span id="freeText16096121381245563442" style="display:none">Philosophical novel from 12th century by Ibn Tufail about a baby born and raised by a deer on an isolated island without any human interaction. The character’s thought process and culture evolution summarize that of humankind from fig leaf moment to faith. Major theme is that all roads lead to god. A controversial view is that Ibn Tufail was an atheist and meant the total opposite, i.e. human civilizations will always create a god of their own even if they start fresh on an island. Short and easy read… a must for its classic and philosophical value in times of early Islam</span>
  <a data-text-id="16096121381245563442" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


